itely in for an adventure....</b></b>\r\n\r\nHere are some next steps:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li dir="ltr">Get your team together.  The more diverse the better.   You can have as many folks on your team as you’d like.</li>\r\n	<li dir="ltr">Get your workspace together.   The more tools of creativity the better.  The more access to things to Deconstruct the better. The more access to late night food and coffee the better.  Also, good internet is key.</li>\r\n	<li dir="ltr">Spend a little time thinking about how to best livestream yourselves. It’s fun, believe us.  We will be sending out some recommendations on cameras to use and some best practices soon.  If you haven’t done this before don’t be afraid...it’s easy.   Costumes, hyjinks, and all varieties of tomfoolery are highly encouraged!   There is also a special award for “best webcast”.</li>\r\n	<li dir="ltr">Check out and like/follow the Deconstruction Facebook and Twitter page.  We will be hinting at topics, competition format, and sharing information leading up to the event. It will be the main way we communicate with teams leading into the event.  We try to post fun stuff, but it''s functional too.  <a href="http://www.facebook.com/thedeconstruction">www.facebook.com/thedeconstruction </a>   <a href="http://twitter.com/deconstruction">twitter.com/Deconstruction</a></li>\r\n	<li dir="ltr">Spend time reading our awesome FAQ (<a href="http://thedeconstruction.org/faq/">http://thedeconstruction.org/faq/</a>) and send us questions so we can add them to this page</li>\r\n	<li dir="ltr">You will be sent a generated Wordpress Login...YOU NEED TO KEEP THIS!   Part of the Deconstruction game format is showing documentation of you project, and how it comes together.   You will have the ability to upload to this Worpress site (or you have the option of using Instructables).   You also have to post your final video there as well for judging.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<b id="internal-source-marker_0.8245036664884537">\r\n</b>Please help us s