(8, 'Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet, consectetur adipiscing elit. Cras quam odio, mattis a tincidunt sit amet, pharetra at lorem. Curabitur nec ante sed magna rutrum venenatis. Nulla facilisi. Etiam a tellus enim, gravida volutpat nibh. Vivamus ac quam tempor nisi dignissim scelerisque. Proin sed dui metus. Quisque vehicula tellus a lectus gravida venenatis sed vitae est.\r\n\r\nDonec ultrices arcu eget velit cursus mattis. Proin auctor dapibus sodales. Pellentesque accumsan mattis magna ac tincidunt. Etiam ac'),
(62, 'akfsakflksajfkl;dmsnaf,mdsnmmmmmnamfndm,anfmd,nam,sndmf,nsm,dfnnfm,n,amndm,fns,mnfmns,mdfnm,nf,mnsm,fnam,nfm,ndfm,ndm,fnndfklnflknermnenklnakren,mrn,mnksdnflknsfmndaf,nd,mfnm,snfd,mnfm,nfndnfekwaenfmnema,ne,ncmnecm,name,n,menra,mnrm,enr,mnaerm,nerm,nemr,n,menrmenr,mwner,mnem,ranm,enra,mnerm,wnemr,nemrnwm,enrmarm,nerm,nam,erm,naer,mnaer,mnm,ern,manrm,enr,merm,nam,nrmn,emnr,em,nrm,narm,nemn,rmn,aerm,nm,n,mnmnmntemna,mndrm,naerm,nema,nr,manrm,naerm,aem,rnaerm,am,nerm,narm,naerm,nam,ner,mnaermn,amn,'),
(92, 'We met accidentally in a gym about 15 years ago. We have held many occupations, played many roles, and licked our passions into infinity, but our most significant quest is to unravel the butter cream murder mystery. '),
(102, 'Sheet Metal Alchemist is a group of artists focusing on interactive installation metal work. With access to Boxshop, Techshop, and the Department of Spontaneous Combustion, the latest in machining technology is fused with traditional shop techniques to create innovative, unique installations. Core members work full time on new installations. For large projects, the experienced core members welcome and train novices young and old for free to inspire a new generation of artists.'),
(131, 'We were finalists in the Red Bull Creation last summer - affectionately (we believe) known as "The Little Red Bull Creation Team that Could" (LRBCTC).   With big hearts, lots of creativity & a shoestring budget, our multigenerational LRBCTC built first an awesome Red Bull Alarm clock, & then a massive spinning marble game.  We didn''t make it to the NY Maker Faire, but we did show that wherever you are, there''s your makerspace!'),
(153, 'We are a team of graduate students, recently escaped from prison.  Today still wanted by our advisors, we survive as solders of making.  If you have a problem, and if you can find us, then you might be able to hire... Alaska thunderfuck.'),
(183, 'We self fund all of our projects, pick through trash, and rip apart old junk to acquire the parts we need. We consist of a few main members, and a larger community of friends who stop in to help.  We want to be makers full-time, we really do.  Alex and Steve are engineering students of opposite types, and Justin has a degree in philosophy and respiratory therapy.  While Justin works at the regional hospital, Alex and I go to school, and all the while we are transforming NSL into this!'),
(199, 'I''m a system integrator. For various industrial or retail devices. Mostly data collection devices. Learned alots of cool things and always amazed to see how uC controller works. Also got interest in mechanical, way back in school time, was trying to build 2 stroke engine, read lots of book, but sadly i dont have much tools and expertise way back then, only able to gather knowledge. Now im married and with two lovely son, elder son like me, he enjoy ripping things apart and see how it works.'),
(212, 'We''re a bunch of thinkers, tweakers and makers fueled by curiosity and the desire to find out what is possible. \r\n\r\nWe are Chris Houlis, Adrian Stewart, Sunny Haynes, John Gratton, Kate McMahon, Angela Hoefenagel and Porsche Herbert-Funk\r\n\r\nWe are bring together the worlds of carpentry, IT, construction, government policy wrangling, social enterprise, art & creative process.  \r\n\r\nWe are more interested in the mash-up than the masterplan. We''d rather be passionate amateurs than professionals.'),
(222, 'We are a band of misfits from Virginia who have banded together to start a compnay like no other.  We plan to offer services to anyone in the community to go from idea to ready to sell products. Most of our team members have met through school and involvement in the FIRST robotics competitions. We bring a diversity of skills all with engineering applications. From bolts and bearings to databases and game engines, we have experienced it all. We are also well versed in repurposing old hardware.'),
(264, 'An interdisciplinary group of professional craftsmen and women who teach the trades. We are old school in many ways, maintaining old machines and techniques so that they may be brought to bear when access to tools and methods stop others. We act as the catalyst providing the key creative links in larger creations. Our group works in all mediums as it is made up of practicing professionals some who no doubt will want to form their own teams but we shall see.'),
(274, 'Stolen from the Wikipedians:\r\n\r\nThe Ouroboros often represents self-reflexivity or cyclicality, especially in the sense of something constantly re-creating itself, the eternal return, and other things perceived as cycles that begin anew as soon as they end (compare with phoenix). It can also represent the idea of primordial unity related to something existing in or persisting from the beginning with such force or qualities it cannot be extinguished.'),
(284, 'We''re just a few friends from highschool. We are artists and engineers and just nerds in general. Our team for the deconstruction consists of Ted Goodell, a tall skinny nerd who does sound engineering and comes from money. Jordan Vogel, she does our math and programming. Sagan Gotberg, our artist and creative person. and lastly Isaac Doubek, the amateur in amateur manufacturing. It helps that he has a giant cnc though. Toghether, like voltron, we are a force to be reckoned with in the makerverse'),
(293, 'We are a bunch of very good friends, all fans of DIY. We met in a french engineering school where we used to organise a small festival each year. We all share a common hobby : creating funny devices from open-source matérials and/or used parts (that''s why we''re interested in The Deconstruction!). Some of us are skilled in mechanics, others in electronics and other are kind of artists. But above all, we''re skilled in having fun ! '),
(308, 'Cameron - Gamer, musician, and programmer.  Met Jeremy playing in an orchestra and now work with him at the day job!\r\nJeremy - Gamer, musician, and programmer.  Met Cameron playing in an orchestra and now work with him at the day job! Met Wesley through Twitter over chatting about D&D, later hired him for his artwork and design services on several board games.\r\nWesley - Gamer, artist, and underwear model.  (Maybe not that last one...) '),
(318, 'Inspired by the ingenuity displayed in South America, we decided to imitate their methods. After many experiments we finally managed it. Wheat paste and paper combined with other accessible materials to create, low cost instruments, such as violins and cellos.\r\n'),
(338, 'MAG Lab is a nonprofit hackerspace in the Pomona, California area. We are a community of technically minded people who love to learn, create and collaborate on making cool things. We want to connect interested members of the local community with equipment and knowledge that they otherwise might not be able to access. No matter what your current skill set or knowledge level, as long as you like to play with technology, there is a place for you here.'),
(348, 'The Defiance Project is a dance company that uses processes of defiance to engage a community of collaborators through personal and collective experiences of presence, connection, and change. Defiance is a lens through which we can experience and interact with expectations, standards, norms, and comfort- regardless of what the nuances of these objects of defiance may be. Choosing to experience through the act of defiance is defiance in and of itself.'),
(361, 'Twin Geeks is the team name for two handsome and inventive makers living in lovely Montreal, Mike and Filip. They like riding bikes, doing science, rummaging through garbage,  and making puns.\r\nMike is a seasoned professional bicycle mechanic and metalworking genius, known to create beauty out of piles of junk metal, and create strange contraptions on two wheels.\r\nFilip is an electronics and software guru, comfortable with anything from microprocessors to vacuum tubes.\r\n\r\n'),
(370, 'We are an intrepid group of young muscular engineers who are devoted to building awesome stuff. Our headquarter is hosted at the rugged Drexel University in Sunny Philadelphia. Our hobbies are long walks on the beach, blowing up stuff, and building things to blow up. We are a fairly new makerspace, but we hope to impress and seduce all the other teams!'),
(379, 'We are The Experimentalists! Our team is made up of a couple (both literally and figuratively) of nerds who enjoy researching, experimenting and finding simple, intuitive solutions. Why "The Experimentalists" you say? Well, because we love to analyze, study and "test out" our hypotheses! Zane is a Mechanical Engineering major, while Charlotte is a Biology major and we both attend CSU, Sacramento. We thoroughly enjoy creating innovative solutions to our everyday problems and we LOVE science!'),
(394, 'We are Electrical Engineering Student from Mercubuana University, we have a robotic grup call KORONA(Komunitas Robot Mercubuana) .\r\nWe was participated a robotic contest in 2012 , we built a hexapod 2DOF robot , we built with Low cost and less time. when I had been participating the contest , I saw a lot of very nice construction of Hexapod robot and they were 3DOF. we were lost the contest , but we are still happy to participate that contest. now for my final test , I have redesign the robot '),
(405, 'we are neighbors, family members, and former classmates at a ritzy private school which had a lot of slogans on a lot of t shirts, but didn''t make much of a difference.   and the class physics project for 8th grade was making a ''submarine hover'' using a soda bottle.\r\n\r\nwe''ve been living in a house that was trashed by licensed contractors, with the blessing of the building dept, but will try to make lemonade out of lemons'),
(445, 'The team is being put together on a "if I make it, they will come" basis.\r\n\r\nDuring Columbus'' first trip to America, sponsored by Spain, he brought back chocolate. It was thrown away because nobody knew what to do with it.  It took anther 200 years before someone thought to make chocolate bars.  \r\n\r\nI look forward to surrounding myself with people here in Spain who aren''t going to wait 200 years for a good idea to happen.\r\n'),
(454, 'Sophomore Mechanical Engineering students from the University of Delaware looking to have some hands on learning.  Michael "Balls" is the Code monkey for the team.  Austin and Ben are roommates that are constantly tinkering in their techie dorm room which includes everything from a 3D printer to a projector.  Mike "Junkin" , Lindsay and Jess are all first time hackers and look to get their hands dirty and learn a lot along the way.  Some more Mechanical Engineering students may stumble in.'),
(464, 'We are the Rabbit Hole Hackerspace, an up and coming hackerspace in Rochester, MN.  Just about every facet of our hackerspace is DIY - from the sectional to the work benches.  Our members are made of engineers, biogeeks, and nerds from IBM and Mayo Clinic!  We''re currently located in the basement of the Tymkrs (http://tymkrs.com) and hope to share our love of subzero temperatures with everyone else!'),
(484, 'John, Kyle, and Chris. We met at superhero training camp! ;) Our very amateur skills are as follows. John: hardware and electronics. Kyle: 3d animation, all things internet,and he also makes killer music. Chris: I.T. specialist in training. '),
(494, 'Bozo Nightmare makes music without thinking too much about it. They embrace steam-of-consciousness, random, improvised, collaborative, in-the-moment, electronic, acoustic, inspired, music. Major influences include Bruce Haack, Berlin-Era David Bowie, Brian Eno, Early Beck, Captain Beefheart, The Flaming Lips, Guided By Voices, etc.'),
(513, 'Our team consists of two women and one gentleman at this time but always open for new team members! Besides myself Terri Strain, there is Teresa Simmons, Casey Mutch, and Walt Callahan. We are basically a group of techies who originally got together for me to teach various software programs, website design, and computer basics to and then ended up finding our mutual love in various crafting genres, i.e., Jewelry making, beading, card making, scrapbooking, etc. Can''t wait to share!'),
(526, 'We''re a group of friends from college, there''s a couple of software engineers, a hardware guy, an app designer and a graphic artist. \r\nLooking to get into open source design and generally just learn! We''re based in Dublin in Ireland (great spot). \r\nAs we''re all pretty new to this we started a website where we''ll be talking about our projects and stuff we''ll be working on.\r\n\r\nOne of us has a terrible secret, which shall be revealed on the night. ');
